# Agent name normalizer corrections

20+ `CANONICAL_NAMES` values in `agent_name_normalizer.py` corrected to match actual upstream `name:` frontmatter:

| Key | Before | After |
|-----|--------|-------|
| `documentation` | `"Documentation"` | `"Documentation Agent"` |
| `ticketing` | `"Ticketing"` | `"ticketing_agent"` |
| `content` | `"Content"` | `"Content Optimization"` |
| `code_analyzer` | `"Code Analyzer"` | `"Code Analysis"` |
| `gcp_ops` | `"GCP Ops"` | `"Google Cloud Ops"` |
| `clerk_ops` | `"Clerk Ops"` | `"Clerk Operations"` |
| `javascript_engineer` | `"JavaScript Engineer"` | `"Javascript Engineer"` |
| `typescript_engineer` | `"TypeScript Engineer"` | `"Typescript Engineer"` |
| `tmux` | `"Tmux"` | `"Tmux Agent"` |

`to_key()` now does a reverse lookup in `CANONICAL_NAMES` instead of deriving from display name (fixes `"Documentation Agent"` -> `"documentation_agent"` producing wrong key; now correctly returns `"documentation"`). `to_task_format()` delegates to `to_key()` then replaces underscores with dashes.
